Resolving Issues with Shipments

Confer with Establishment Representatives

1. Identify the problem: Upon receiving a shipment, inspect it thoroughly to identify any damages, shortages, or nonconformities to specifications. 2. Document the issue: Record the details of the problem, including the shipment number, date, and description of the issue. 3. Contact the representative: Reach out to the establishment representative responsible for the shipment and notify them of the issue. 4. Collaborate to resolve: Work with the representative to resolve the issue, which may involve inspecting the shipment together, documenting the damage or shortage, and discussing possible solutions.

Correspondence and Follow-up

1. Communicate clearly: Clearly and concisely communicate the issue and proposed solution to the representative. 2. Follow up: Schedule a follow-up meeting or call to ensure the issue is being addressed and to provide any necessary updates. 3. Verify resolution: Confirm that the issue has been resolved to the satisfaction of both parties.
